Program: Omnibus
Title: Moon Landings
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jn8
Last Broadcast Date: 12 July 1989
How American president John F Kennedy came to the decision to put man on the moon. A look back at the space race on the 20th anniversary of man's first moon walk. Includes an interview with Thomas O Paine, head of NASA during the moon landings. Picture: Astronaut on moon, Credit: Getty Images